1
00:00:00,477 --> 00:00:02,000
The lump on your neck...

2
00:00:02,508 --> 00:00:04,680
I think you should have a biopsy.

3
00:00:04,920 --> 00:00:08,240
You'll be fine.
I'll be waiting for the good news.

4
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:10,720
It's 50/50, Mom.

5
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:13,160
Anything could happen.

6
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:16,800
If anything happens to me,
You have to look after Ohn.

7
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:19,240
You two care for
each other so much.

8
00:00:19,695 --> 00:00:21,489
The publisher called and said

9
00:00:21,489 --> 00:00:24,222
the spin-off project
has been greenlit.

10
00:00:24,222 --> 00:00:26,960
I'll get to write
a special Duckman series!

11
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:30,450
- Yay! Congrats, Ohn!
- Hey, that's cool!

12
00:00:54,622 --> 00:00:56,120
"I can't sleep tonight."

13
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:01,600
"It's a night
I'd rather not remember."

14
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,680
Mr. Jira, the doctor
is ready for you.

15
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,762
Mr. Jira?

16
00:01:58,762 --> 00:02:00,589
Mr. Jira.

17
00:02:21,905 --> 00:02:23,821
The results of your biopsy are in.

18
00:02:30,106 --> 00:02:31,720
No cancer cells were found.

19
00:02:34,848 --> 00:02:37,560
From now on, you need to start
taking better care of yourself.

20
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:40,240
Go to bed early.
Control your sugar intake.

21
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:43,320
Try brisk walking
for 30 minutes a day.

22
00:02:44,101 --> 00:02:47,440
Doing cardio 2 to 3 days a week,
does that sound doable for you?

23
00:02:47,952 --> 00:02:49,440
Absolutely.

24
00:02:50,535 --> 00:02:53,055
Don't forget to bring your partner
for a follow-up as well.

25
00:02:53,055 --> 00:02:55,640
I intend to bring him to exercise
with me every day anyway.

26
00:02:57,417 --> 00:03:00,400
Taking care of each other
as a pair is even better.

27
00:03:01,479 --> 00:03:03,960
Cardio for 30 minutes every day.

28
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,240
Staying strong.

29
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,586
I'll have a leg cramp for sure.

30
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,680
Why does the morning world
seem to have no mercy on me at all?

31
00:03:20,057 --> 00:03:21,256
Well...

32
00:03:21,256 --> 00:03:23,040
Hey, tie your shoelaces properly.

33
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:25,140
Three laps of brisk walking,
and stop complaining.

34
00:03:25,140 --> 00:03:28,480
Gosh, Jee. Let me rest a bit.

35
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,480
Ohn...!

36
00:03:31,755 --> 00:03:34,240
We haven't even been
walking for 10 minutes.

37
00:03:34,547 --> 00:03:37,114
We should walk for three laps,
about ten minutes each.

38
00:03:37,114 --> 00:03:38,660
Then do some light weights.

39
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:42,045
That's only 2.5 hours a week.

40
00:03:42,045 --> 00:03:44,360
Oh, Jee.

41
00:03:45,164 --> 00:03:47,040
Let's take it one step at a time.

42
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:50,200
Like, step by step,
I'll sneak back up to the condo?

43
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,260
Hey!

44
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:56,253
I'm still doing the workout program
that A set for me every day.

45
00:03:56,253 --> 00:03:58,527
And now, you're adding more?

46
00:03:58,527 --> 00:04:00,100
Oh, come on.

47
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:03,540
Look, do you see Uncle Ood
and Auntie Jib over there?

48
00:04:03,540 --> 00:04:06,800
They're in their 70s
but still exercise every morning.

49
00:04:08,073 --> 00:04:09,927
One, two, three... there.

50
00:04:09,927 --> 00:04:12,447
- That's their business, isn't it?
- Hey!

51
00:04:12,447 --> 00:04:14,516
This cardio thing...

52
00:04:14,914 --> 00:04:17,901
Is there no other way?
Is it just walking and running?

53
00:04:17,901 --> 00:04:22,660
Well, there's swimming, cycling,

54
00:04:23,210 --> 00:04:26,560
What else? Aerobics.

55
00:04:28,173 --> 00:04:29,433
Jump rope, too.

56
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,920
Come on.

57
00:04:50,991 --> 00:04:53,909
When I asked you
to walk three laps,

58
00:04:53,909 --> 00:04:55,989
you acted like you're dying.

59
00:04:55,989 --> 00:04:57,401
But as soon as the music starts,

60
00:04:57,401 --> 00:05:00,280
your body just moves, huh?

61
00:05:07,052 --> 00:05:09,359
Don't tease me, Jee.

62
00:05:09,359 --> 00:05:11,320
I'll try again. It could be better.

63
00:05:24,673 --> 00:05:25,786
Mission accomplished.

64
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:27,600
Survived another morning.

65
00:05:30,913 --> 00:05:32,340
"Skipping gym?
Double up tomorrow."

66
00:05:32,340 --> 00:05:33,592
This old man.

67
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,440
Isn't this a bit much?

68
00:05:36,497 --> 00:05:39,537
Will I survive long enough
to get healthy?

69
00:05:45,606 --> 00:05:46,606
Hey!

70
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,120
Mindy?

71
00:05:53,055 --> 00:05:54,055
You...

72
00:05:55,961 --> 00:05:57,840
You slept here?

73
00:05:59,137 --> 00:06:01,120
How long have you
been sleeping here?

74
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:07,040
"What was all that before?"

75
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:10,040
"Do you actually like me,
or are you just waiting for a man?"

76
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:15,200
I'm done. Talk to whoever you want.

77
00:06:15,382 --> 00:06:17,400
Just leave.
I'm not getting involved.

78
00:06:26,549 --> 00:06:28,480
I've been sleeping here
for several nights now.

79
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:50,560
You want to let
Mindy stay here for a while?

80
00:06:51,547 --> 00:06:52,560
Mmm-hmm.

81
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Just for about two weeks.

82
00:06:57,156 --> 00:07:01,520
She's in a real mess right now.

83
00:07:05,221 --> 00:07:06,600
Please?

84
00:07:11,249 --> 00:07:12,249
Fine.

85
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:16,160
Thanks a lot, Jee.

86
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:18,160
Come here. Get your reward.

87
00:07:21,364 --> 00:07:24,929
It's actually good.
I'll have another workout buddy.

88
00:07:25,915 --> 00:07:29,640
Gosh, how much more fit
do you want to get?

89
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:34,507
I can't imagine
what state Mindy will be in.

90
00:07:34,507 --> 00:07:35,720
She's all mine.

91
00:07:38,385 --> 00:07:40,200
That works for me.
Now I can slack off.

92
00:07:47,929 --> 00:07:50,720
Just a few more minutes.

93
00:07:51,142 --> 00:07:53,880
It's not time
to face the world yet.

94
00:07:58,376 --> 00:07:59,960
Mmm. Look at you.

95
00:08:01,034 --> 00:08:03,114
Come on...

96
00:08:03,706 --> 00:08:04,706
Ta-da!

97
00:08:05,097 --> 00:08:07,144
Let there be light... Now!

98
00:08:07,144 --> 00:08:10,744
Stop teasing me.

99
00:08:10,744 --> 00:08:13,380
- Hehe...
- Close the curtains.

100
00:08:13,380 --> 00:08:17,022
The weather is lovely.
Let's go get some morning sun.

101
00:08:17,022 --> 00:08:19,605
It's a shame to stay in.
Even Charcoal is already up.

102
00:08:19,605 --> 00:08:21,342
That's Charcoal's business!

103
00:08:24,873 --> 00:08:25,893
Yes?

104
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:29,842
- Can I use the shower?
- Sure, come on in.

105
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,447
- Jee.
- Hmm?

106
00:08:34,447 --> 00:08:37,000
Are you entering a marathon?

107
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:42,120
No, just some light exercise.
Walking on the grass,

108
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:45,379
getting some sun,
and waking up the soul.

109
00:08:48,986 --> 00:08:50,213
Wake it up, then.

110
00:08:55,387 --> 00:08:59,174
Mindy, take your time
in the shower.

111
00:08:59,174 --> 00:09:03,920
Clean every nook and cranny.
No rush. Wash your hair too.

112
00:09:08,518 --> 00:09:10,120
Take a long time, right? Fine.

113
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,753
Hmph. Ready...

114
00:09:13,753 --> 00:09:14,882
Soul awakening!

115
00:09:15,345 --> 00:09:18,161
Wake up! Wake up!

116
00:09:19,945 --> 00:09:22,923
- I'm awake! I'm awake!
- Wake up, wake up!

117
00:09:22,923 --> 00:09:24,112
I'm awake, I'm awake!

118
00:09:25,945 --> 00:09:28,280
- Jee, I'm awake!
- Oh, you're awake now?

119
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,440
This is so refreshing.

120
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:39,240
Let's walk a bit more.
It'll be really nice.

121
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,240
Yes.

122
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:42,160
Hi, there!

123
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:46,240
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

124
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:47,520
How are you guys?

125
00:09:48,257 --> 00:09:50,680
Got a new member with you?

126
00:09:51,149 --> 00:09:52,520
That's right.

127
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:56,440
You're so fit. Morning walk
will surely keep you healthy.

128
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,840
Are you heading back already?

129
00:09:58,840 --> 00:09:59,840
Not yet.

130
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:02,080
Could I leave these
with you for a moment?

131
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:03,120
Sure.

132
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:08,833
Today, we'll start with
15 minutes of brisk walking

133
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:11,040
along with some
light water bottle weights.

134
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:12,120
Okay.

135
00:10:14,088 --> 00:10:16,755
Now, now, take it easy.

136
00:10:16,755 --> 00:10:19,960
Don't force it. Just move
with your body's rhythm.

137
00:10:21,076 --> 00:10:24,220
Three, two, one... go!

138
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:26,860
Okay.

139
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:27,900
Let's go.

140
00:10:54,167 --> 00:10:56,455
See? The morning sun
feels really good.

141
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:05,880
It's morning.
Time to get up and move on.

142
00:11:19,111 --> 00:11:20,280
Mmm-hmm.

143
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,520
Ohn?

144
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,560
Jee?

145
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,440
Ohn.

146
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:42,840
Drink up.

147
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,566
I need to use the bathroom, okay?

148
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,653
"Do you actually like me,
or are you just waiting for a man?"

149
00:12:10,011 --> 00:12:11,125
Whoa!

150
00:12:15,982 --> 00:12:16,982
Oops!

151
00:12:25,862 --> 00:12:27,915
I'm sorry! So sorry!

152
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:46,920
How are things? Have you eaten yet?

153
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,400
Not yet.

154
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,000
Did I miss something?

155
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:08,360
Is there something fun going on?

156
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:11,560
Nothing. Nothing at all...

157
00:13:14,607 --> 00:13:15,607
Hmm?

158
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,480
It's just...

159
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:23,120
Someone was in a rush
to get to the bathroom.

160
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:25,560
And then...

161
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:28,200
And then...

162
00:13:28,627 --> 00:13:29,720
saw...

163
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,840
the naked truth.

164
00:13:37,478 --> 00:13:39,880
It wasn't on purpose.

165
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,920
I really didn't mean to.

166
00:13:44,272 --> 00:13:45,592
They call it...

167
00:13:46,802 --> 00:13:50,640
True intimacy.

168
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,339
It's okay, right, Ohn?

169
00:13:59,170 --> 00:14:00,324
Okay.

170
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:06,294
Let's just call it full disclosure.

171
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:08,840
So we'll get close even faster.

172
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,760
Oh, Mindy.

173
00:14:37,177 --> 00:14:38,297
Still not sleepy?

174
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,960
Not yet. Maybe, in a bit.

175
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,520
Well, then. Here.

176
00:14:41,869 --> 00:14:43,009
Uh-oh.

177
00:14:43,371 --> 00:14:45,200
Tea, tea, tea, tea.

178
00:14:45,580 --> 00:14:46,600
Tea, tea, tea, tea.

179
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:48,240
- What kind of tea, Jee?
- This is...

180
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:51,407
Chamomile tea.

181
00:14:51,407 --> 00:14:52,873
We all have some.

182
00:14:52,873 --> 00:14:54,911
- It smells wonderful.
- Enjoy the aroma.

183
00:14:54,911 --> 00:14:57,207
- Smells good.
- It'll help you sleep well.

184
00:14:58,473 --> 00:15:00,527
- Thank you, Jee.
- You're welcome.

185
00:15:00,527 --> 00:15:02,274
- Thanks a lot, Jee.
- Sure.

186
00:15:02,274 --> 00:15:04,680
- I'm heading to bed now.
- Okay, goodnight.

187
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:12,887
- Oh, okay.
- Hey, wait!

188
00:15:12,887 --> 00:15:13,920
Mmm.

189
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,680
- What!
- Just kidding!

190
00:15:16,849 --> 00:15:18,440
Okay.

191
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:21,320
Make yourselves at home.

192
00:15:21,715 --> 00:15:24,048
- Night, night.
- Night, night.

193
00:15:27,450 --> 00:15:28,450
Ohn.

194
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,120
He seems like such a calm person.

195
00:15:34,155 --> 00:15:37,507
Well, not about everything.

196
00:15:37,507 --> 00:15:40,000
But he's always kind.

197
00:15:42,038 --> 00:15:45,600
Come to think of it, I haven't felt
this at ease in a long time.

198
00:15:46,697 --> 00:15:48,160
Ever since...

199
00:15:48,978 --> 00:15:49,978
Hmm?

200
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,040
Ever since back then...

201
00:16:01,262 --> 00:16:02,955
You've been lying to me?

202
00:16:05,657 --> 00:16:06,840
Lying about what? I...

203
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:09,080
Why didn't you tell me
that you like men, too?

204
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:14,440
How can I ever believe you again
that you truly love me?

205
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:16,986
I love you.

206
00:16:17,851 --> 00:16:19,040
It's the truth.

207
00:16:21,082 --> 00:16:22,671
I saw it, you know.

208
00:16:23,587 --> 00:16:26,520
The way you look at men
when you talk to them.

209
00:16:30,959 --> 00:16:32,260
It was nothing.

210
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:35,080
Nothing?

211
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:38,800
When the evidence
is right in front of me?

212
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:41,082
When we first started dating,

213
00:16:41,082 --> 00:16:42,802
I saw you sneaking glances
at other women.

214
00:16:42,802 --> 00:16:45,595
I could handle that thinking
you liked looking at pretty girls.

215
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,164
But men?

216
00:16:48,164 --> 00:16:50,986
You look at men, and you like them.

217
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,560
But you never told me.

218
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:57,040
It doesn't matter at all, Liu.

219
00:16:57,040 --> 00:17:00,007
Whether I like women or men...

220
00:17:00,007 --> 00:17:01,240
Do you know why?

221
00:17:01,766 --> 00:17:03,640
Because I chose to be with you.

222
00:17:03,986 --> 00:17:06,233
And I have no intention
of ever leaving you.

223
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,402
It does matter.

224
00:17:08,785 --> 00:17:10,958
If two people are going to
spend their lives together,

225
00:17:10,958 --> 00:17:13,360
but can't open up or
tell each other the truth,

226
00:17:13,824 --> 00:17:15,560
how can they ever make it work?

227
00:17:16,069 --> 00:17:18,800
You should have been honest
with me from the start.

228
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:22,319
But you stayed silent.

229
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:26,080
You never asked
if I could help with anything.

230
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:29,360
You kept everything to yourself.

231
00:17:32,819 --> 00:17:34,666
I didn't want you to worry.

232
00:17:36,167 --> 00:17:37,367
I care about you.

233
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:39,680
I wanted to protect you.

234
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:43,480
I'm right here with you.

235
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,160
With me?

236
00:17:47,593 --> 00:17:49,280
But you were never really present.

237
00:17:58,325 --> 00:17:59,325
Just go.

238
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:06,920
It was my mistake.
I didn't tell her from the start.

239
00:18:10,421 --> 00:18:13,560
Is there no way to talk it out?

240
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:16,052
She's given up,

241
00:18:16,052 --> 00:18:18,076
and already started
seeing other people.

242
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:31,160
I brought another friend today.

243
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:32,633
Okay.

244
00:18:33,498 --> 00:18:34,511
Oh!

245
00:18:34,511 --> 00:18:36,280
- Ahh...
- Jira. Ohn.

246
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:41,560
Hmm?
Who'd you bring to join us today?

247
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,600
A friend.

248
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,640
A, this is Mindy. Mindy, this is A.

249
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:47,960
She's here to try it out.
Take good care of her.

250
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:52,400
Easy. She's about to find out.

251
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:58,120
Keep your back at a 45° angle.
Then push yourself up.

252
00:19:00,858 --> 00:19:02,880
Yes, then down.

253
00:19:03,902 --> 00:19:07,115
Okay, and up. Keep going.

254
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:14,720
Ohn, last time
you couldn't even lift this.

255
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:16,360
Today, you're like
a different person.

256
00:19:16,710 --> 00:19:19,897
Impressive! Want to add some more?

257
00:19:19,897 --> 00:19:22,680
Whoa! No thanks, Coach.

258
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:25,653
Let me just survive this set first.

259
00:19:25,653 --> 00:19:27,480
Okay. Keep at it then.

260
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:28,918
Great job!

261
00:19:28,918 --> 00:19:30,960
Your back and leg muscles
are looking good.

262
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:34,000
Push yourself up.

263
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,440
Okay, that's enough.

264
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:49,880
Are you sure you've
never done this before?

265
00:19:51,576 --> 00:19:53,160
You don't look like a beginner.

266
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,440
"Yes?"

267
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,880
Liu, I'm sorry.

268
00:20:38,140 --> 00:20:41,800
Can we talk about the house?

269
00:21:03,490 --> 00:21:08,030
"I'm not trying to take your money.
Give me some time to process."

270
00:21:30,799 --> 00:21:32,225
Give me a second, everyone.

271
00:21:39,866 --> 00:21:41,880
Just a few more minutes, Duckman.

272
00:21:45,670 --> 00:21:50,154
"Incoming call"

273
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:51,780
Hello?

274
00:21:52,968 --> 00:21:57,120
Yeah, I didn't forget.
We'll all go together.

275
00:21:57,720 --> 00:22:00,040
We'll clear out Mae Champi's room.

276
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:01,200
So we can vacate the room.

277
00:22:02,218 --> 00:22:05,080
Yeah, okay. See you tomorrow.

278
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:14,160
Editor.

279
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:23,800
Ready?

280
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:25,880
Yeah.

281
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:39,880
Is this really everything she had?

282
00:22:40,345 --> 00:22:42,040
Yeah, I think that's about it.

283
00:22:42,970 --> 00:22:44,880
Let's pack it all up.

284
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:48,360
She used to say...

285
00:22:48,934 --> 00:22:50,339
that when she died,

286
00:22:50,339 --> 00:22:52,807
she wanted help moving her things.

287
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:56,640
Back then, we just laughed.
We thought she was joking.

288
00:23:10,739 --> 00:23:14,106
"Hey Fabs! Come here."

289
00:23:14,106 --> 00:23:17,739
I brought you some lip balm.
Wear it when you play volleyball.

290
00:23:17,739 --> 00:23:20,680
Win or lose doesn't matter.
We have to look beautiful first.

291
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:27,800
Life, isn't it?
Getting to know one another,

292
00:23:28,509 --> 00:23:29,680
taking care of one another,

293
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:31,920
and in the end,

294
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:34,360
we part ways.

295
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:47,720
Oh, hello everyone.

296
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:50,129
Hello. Hello.

297
00:23:51,674 --> 00:23:54,067
I didn't see you at the funeral.

298
00:23:54,067 --> 00:23:58,060
I just got back from a friend's
funeral out in the countryside.

299
00:23:58,060 --> 00:24:00,493
At our age, we are
passing away one by one.

300
00:24:00,493 --> 00:24:03,653
I'm bringing these flowers
to pay her my respects.

301
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:09,160
We talked every evening
for about 10 years.

302
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:12,640
With Mae Champi gone,
I'm feeling quite lonely too.

303
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:15,801
She used to say...

304
00:24:15,801 --> 00:24:18,720
that she wanted to go
without being a burden to anyone.

305
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:22,240
But when it comes down to it,
we still rely on others, don't we?

306
00:24:24,868 --> 00:24:25,868
In this alley...

307
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:29,333
there're people of
all genders and ages.

308
00:24:29,333 --> 00:24:31,357
Mostly, we're here, waiting,

309
00:24:32,920 --> 00:24:35,652
waiting for work,
waiting for relatives to visit,

310
00:24:35,652 --> 00:24:37,812
some even waiting for
their elderly allowance.

311
00:24:37,812 --> 00:24:40,152
In a way, we're waiting for hope.

312
00:24:43,216 --> 00:24:44,529
What about you, Taew?

313
00:24:44,529 --> 00:24:46,800
Me? I'm waiting for work.

314
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:49,266
I'm lucky I still have my strength.

315
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:52,960
Even though I'm alone,
I can still do general odd jobs.

316
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:56,640
I've been a cleaner, even a mover.

317
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:58,600
I'm not picky about work.

318
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:03,520
But now that I'm older,
not many people want to hire me.

319
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:15,920
Mae Champi is gone.

320
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:20,160
But Taew is still pushing on.

321
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:24,040
Taew is tougher than she looks.

322
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,480
A real fighter.

323
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:28,760
Mae Champi and Taew
lived by themselves for so long.

324
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,440
Impressive.

325
00:25:32,320 --> 00:25:33,440
Growing old alone...

326
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:36,320
is no easy feat.

327
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:40,850
But they were lucky

328
00:25:40,850 --> 00:25:42,920
to have the community's support.

329
00:25:44,295 --> 00:25:46,366
If they waited
only for government aid,

330
00:25:46,366 --> 00:25:47,786
it wouldn't be in time.

331
00:25:47,786 --> 00:25:50,840
Taew isn't the type
to just sit idly by.

332
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:55,200
Just give her a chance,
she's ready to stand on her own.

333
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:57,200
She's not waiting for handouts.

334
00:25:57,580 --> 00:25:58,587
Exactly.

335
00:25:58,587 --> 00:26:01,420
If we don't help each other,
how would she survive?

336
00:26:05,522 --> 00:26:07,320
And when we really get old,

337
00:26:08,346 --> 00:26:10,679
what state do we have to be in
to not be miserable?

338
00:26:13,331 --> 00:26:14,331
Well…

339
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:18,120
You don't have to be much. Just...

340
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:22,644
Live alone quietly,
writing songs now and then,

341
00:26:22,644 --> 00:26:25,360
and wait for the cats
to come for their dinner.

342
00:26:25,810 --> 00:26:27,303
That's it.
I probably won't be sad.

343
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:29,640
Maybe.

344
00:26:30,552 --> 00:26:34,680
Hey, Thai. We are planning
to build a house upcountry.

345
00:26:35,524 --> 00:26:37,280
Want to build a house next to mine?

346
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:39,820
That sounds nice.

347
00:26:39,820 --> 00:26:42,794
But I have to consult my cat first.

348
00:26:42,794 --> 00:26:44,818
They are very attached
to their territory.

349
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:48,467
Hey, I haven't asked Charcoal yet!

350
00:26:48,467 --> 00:26:50,680
Jee, we haven't asked Charcoal.

351
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:54,620
That one just moved in.
He can handle a change of scenery.

352
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:55,840
- Really?
- Yeah.

353
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:00,173
If I didn't have to move abroad,

354
00:27:00,173 --> 00:27:04,360
building a house near you guys
would be my dream.

355
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:07,840
But honestly, I can live anywhere,

356
00:27:08,120 --> 00:27:10,120
as long as I have Nidnoi with me.

357
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,760
To be able to laugh a bit,
that would be okay.

358
00:27:15,009 --> 00:27:16,009
Maybe.

359
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:20,000
Get enough sleep,

360
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,640
eat well, and exercise moderately.

361
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:26,160
So your body stays strong.

362
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:28,507
You won't end up bedridden

363
00:27:28,507 --> 00:27:30,531
and becoming a burden
to those around you.

364
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:33,120
Maybe.

365
00:27:42,867 --> 00:27:44,240
Can we have our ball back, please?

366
00:27:45,890 --> 00:27:47,080
- Let me.
- Mmm.

367
00:27:49,557 --> 00:27:51,880
- Whoa!
- What a serve!

368
00:27:54,487 --> 00:27:58,320
Even though I'm old,
I'm still strong for your age.

369
00:28:00,440 --> 00:28:01,440
Maybe.

370
00:28:03,591 --> 00:28:06,071
You guys want to play?

371
00:28:06,486 --> 00:28:07,507
- Come on!
- Yeah.

372
00:28:07,507 --> 00:28:08,707
- Let's go, Chon.
- Serious?

373
00:28:08,707 --> 00:28:10,000
- Yeah.
- Alright.

374
00:28:12,280 --> 00:28:14,551
Come on, "Spectrum Fabulous"!

375
00:28:14,551 --> 00:28:16,320
Woo-hoo!

376
00:28:37,303 --> 00:28:39,880
Oh, excellent!

377
00:29:03,465 --> 00:29:04,600
For the new single,

378
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:06,833
I'm going to make it R&B.

379
00:29:06,833 --> 00:29:08,833
- Really?
- Yes.

380
00:29:08,833 --> 00:29:10,613
I want to change the look.

381
00:29:10,613 --> 00:29:12,127
- Mmm.
- Something much cooler.

382
00:29:12,127 --> 00:29:13,145
That sounds great.

383
00:29:13,697 --> 00:29:15,880
As for the lyric…

384
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:21,200
- Hello, Taew!
- Hello.

385
00:29:22,120 --> 00:29:24,647
Hello, Mr. Thai. Thank you so much.

386
00:29:24,647 --> 00:29:26,113
You are very welcome.

387
00:29:26,113 --> 00:29:27,687
- Hello, Taew.
- Hello.

388
00:29:27,687 --> 00:29:30,726
Today is your first day.
I'll show you to the kitchen first.

389
00:29:30,726 --> 00:29:32,753
Thank you so much. I'll do my best.

390
00:29:32,753 --> 00:29:33,784
Okay.

391
00:29:34,199 --> 00:29:35,659
- I'll leave her with you.
- Got it.

392
00:29:35,659 --> 00:29:36,825
This way, please.

393
00:29:45,946 --> 00:29:48,379
Would you be interested
in a housekeeping job at my office?

394
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:51,080
The previous maid just quit.

395
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:54,000
Will they be okay with me?

396
00:29:55,410 --> 00:29:56,440
Of course.

397
00:29:57,720 --> 00:30:00,200
Thank you so much.
I'll give it a try.

398
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:02,120
Sure.

399
00:30:22,544 --> 00:30:24,360
Still going!

400
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:27,120
Whoa...

401
00:30:30,663 --> 00:30:35,640
Look at that! No leg tremors.
Muscles are starting to show.

402
00:30:38,942 --> 00:30:39,942
Jee.

403
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:45,087
You coaching me through my run,
and you watching him dance,

404
00:30:45,087 --> 00:30:47,160
- Yeah?
- it's like two different people.

405
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:49,560
Hey now! Come on.

406
00:30:49,560 --> 00:30:52,833
This is my cardio.

407
00:30:52,833 --> 00:30:55,360
Yeah, yeah...

408
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:57,880
Just don't overdo it.

409
00:30:58,588 --> 00:31:03,080
If you strain your muscles,
don't say I didn't warn you.

410
00:31:08,224 --> 00:31:09,304
Hey!

411
00:31:09,304 --> 00:31:10,560
Yes, Coach!

412
00:31:11,025 --> 00:31:13,332
- That final pose was beautiful.
- Do that again!

413
00:31:13,332 --> 00:31:15,971
- Strike a pose.
- I'm exhausted.

414
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:18,606
Extend the legs.

415
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:23,080
- Extend your legs.
- This is all I've got.

416
00:31:24,290 --> 00:31:26,170
- Arms back.
- Stretch back.

417
00:31:26,650 --> 00:31:28,250
Yeah, stretch to the back.

418
00:31:28,916 --> 00:31:29,916
That's the limit!

419
00:31:30,872 --> 00:31:33,079
"Planning your life today"

420
00:31:33,079 --> 00:31:35,625
"means you won't have to
rely on luck in the future."

421
00:31:35,625 --> 00:31:38,360
"And you won't have to wait for
your body to send warning signs"

422
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:40,360
"before you start
taking care of yourself."

423
00:31:48,566 --> 00:31:50,379
"My own space"

424
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:23,960
Someone once said...

425
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:28,360
stopping is the art of moving.

426
00:32:29,213 --> 00:32:30,213
It's true.

427
00:32:32,353 --> 00:32:34,320
But when the time is right…

428
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:37,720
I have to move, move, move, move!

429
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:41,640
Mindy,

430
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:43,960
go to sleep now.

431
00:33:00,367 --> 00:33:01,640
Ahh…

432
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:05,560
Overall, I'm doing okay.
Right on plan.

433
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:07,973
Social Security,

434
00:33:07,973 --> 00:33:10,560
Provident Fund, and Mutual Funds,

435
00:33:11,433 --> 00:33:13,680
all contributions are up to date.

436
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:17,360
- That's great, Jee.
- Mmm.

437
00:33:18,832 --> 00:33:20,159
But as for me,

438
00:33:20,597 --> 00:33:22,520
it's not quite hitting the target.

439
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:25,080
Let me see.

440
00:33:26,647 --> 00:33:29,120
Umm, this one.

441
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:36,940
No debt, and you have savings.

442
00:33:36,940 --> 00:33:38,520
You can make this work.

443
00:33:43,907 --> 00:33:48,320
Whoa! 2.4 million baht in savings!

444
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:51,640
1.2 million in RMF.

445
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:55,507
- And 1 million in life insurance.
- Mmm-hmm.

446
00:33:55,507 --> 00:33:58,780
- The mortgage's down to only 400K.
- Exactly.

447
00:33:58,780 --> 00:34:03,280
You've worked hard. Well done!

448
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:06,335
Well, I used AI, Mr. Ohn.

449
00:34:06,335 --> 00:34:07,868
- What?
- Mmm-hmm.

450
00:34:07,868 --> 00:34:10,040
You're not afraid
it'll steal your data?

451
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:14,367
No. I just used it
to help find information.

452
00:34:14,367 --> 00:34:16,960
I'm not giving my personal data.

453
00:34:23,680 --> 00:34:26,240
My work is so unpredictable.

454
00:34:27,922 --> 00:34:30,549
That's why we have to
help each other.

455
00:34:30,549 --> 00:34:33,715
You have your Social Security.

456
00:34:33,715 --> 00:34:35,875
We try to top up
the mutual funds every year.

457
00:34:35,875 --> 00:34:37,689
Putting ours together,
we'll be fine.

458
00:34:37,689 --> 00:34:40,342
And we both have health insurance.

459
00:34:40,342 --> 00:34:41,362
Right?

460
00:34:41,362 --> 00:34:43,742
The emergency fund
is separate, and... oh!

461
00:34:50,680 --> 00:34:54,840
This one, I've named you
as the beneficiary.

462
00:35:01,200 --> 00:35:03,800
I set it up
the day the doctor told me…

463
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:05,920
it wasn't cancer.

464
00:35:10,502 --> 00:35:11,702
Same here.

465
00:35:12,480 --> 00:35:15,640
When I got home that day,
I did the same thing.

466
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:25,320
Yes, that's right.

467
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:28,160
Room 502.

468
00:35:30,680 --> 00:35:32,560
Okay, thank you very much.

469
00:35:41,001 --> 00:35:44,223
Ohn is working from home today.

470
00:35:50,099 --> 00:35:53,739
"Ohn, I've got a place now."

471
00:36:05,037 --> 00:36:07,257
"Liu: the paperwork's done."

472
00:36:07,257 --> 00:36:12,344
"See you Sat. 2 p.m.
We'll be free from each other."

473
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:15,600
"Finally, it's time to move on."

474
00:36:23,563 --> 00:36:24,825
Alright, cheers!

475
00:36:24,825 --> 00:36:26,800
Cheers!

476
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:34,560
For giving me a roof over my head
for these past weeks,

477
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:37,440
thank you both so much.

478
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:41,900
For giving me a place to stay,
a kind heart, and a place to stand.

479
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:47,246
Today we celebrate my new home
and a fresh start at last.

480
00:36:50,020 --> 00:36:51,700
Congratulations, Mindy.

481
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:53,640
This place...

482
00:36:55,040 --> 00:36:56,480
is like another home, you know.

483
00:36:57,053 --> 00:37:00,800
Well, they say home is where...

484
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:06,000
the heart is.
It's not just a place to stay.

485
00:37:07,392 --> 00:37:11,472
Whoa, Jee, that's quite poetic!

486
00:37:11,472 --> 00:37:12,959
- Mmm.
- Seriously,...

487
00:37:12,959 --> 00:37:15,099
have you been reading
Chinese wuxia novels lately?

488
00:37:15,099 --> 00:37:16,400
Total Gu Long vibes.

489
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:19,440
I merely feel it.

490
00:37:20,419 --> 00:37:23,040
There it is! Obviously.

491
00:37:25,139 --> 00:37:28,760
I'm so lucky to be here.

492
00:37:31,520 --> 00:37:34,800
When Liu kicked me out,

493
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:37,360
it felt like...

494
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:41,760
everything I worked for
just collapsed.

495
00:37:42,954 --> 00:37:46,320
It felt like my life
had tripped and fallen.

496
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:49,560
But you know, having you two

497
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:54,680
was like a cushion
that softened the impact.

498
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:56,640
Thank you so much.

499
00:37:57,865 --> 00:37:59,865
You're always welcome here, Mindy.

500
00:38:00,232 --> 00:38:02,840
Actually, the two of us
have been looking at houses too.

501
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:06,227
Somewhere on the outskirts
where it's quiet.

502
00:38:06,227 --> 00:38:09,825
We plan to move out
before we get too decrepit.

503
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:12,913
What?

504
00:38:12,913 --> 00:38:14,967
Who's getting decrepit?

505
00:38:14,967 --> 00:38:18,233
Hey, I can still
do dance challenges!

506
00:38:18,233 --> 00:38:19,667
Hmm?

507
00:38:19,667 --> 00:38:21,113
Go ahead and
be decrepit by yourself.

508
00:38:21,113 --> 00:38:22,280
Oh, really?

509
00:38:23,423 --> 00:38:25,229
Are you two going to
register your marriage?

510
00:38:27,200 --> 00:38:28,520
If you haven't yet...

511
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:32,140
and you're really going to
buy a house together,

512
00:38:32,140 --> 00:38:35,280
don't forget to make
a property agreement.

513
00:38:37,463 --> 00:38:39,240
Just to keep things clear.

514
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:41,880
Define who owns what by law.

515
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:44,480
So there's no mess
to deal with later.

516
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:49,200
And a joint loan account
is also a good option.

517
00:38:53,040 --> 00:38:55,720
It doesn't mean
you don't trust each other.

518
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:57,560
It's more like a safeguard.

519
00:38:58,120 --> 00:39:01,560
Because talking about it
while you're still in love

520
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:02,960
is so much easier.

521
00:39:05,237 --> 00:39:06,480
Take note of that.

522
00:39:07,177 --> 00:39:11,010
Talking about money
is a normal thing.

523
00:39:11,010 --> 00:39:12,600
Don't get bored of it.

524
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:16,160
- Okay.
- Mmm-hmm.

525
00:39:18,974 --> 00:39:20,840
Thank you so much, Mindy.

526
00:39:21,349 --> 00:39:22,627
- You're welcome.
- Come on.

527
00:39:23,148 --> 00:39:24,615
- Dig in!
- Let's eat.

528
00:39:24,615 --> 00:39:26,480
Help yourself!

529
00:39:27,464 --> 00:39:28,624
Looks delicious.

530
00:39:28,624 --> 00:39:30,998
Ohn, are you free tomorrow?

531
00:39:31,578 --> 00:39:33,640
There's something
I'd like to ask your help with.

532
00:39:40,953 --> 00:39:43,480
Let me reiterate the terms
one more time.

533
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:46,880
Miss Liu will repay
the money to Miss Mindy

534
00:39:47,240 --> 00:39:48,880
within 6 months, interest-free,

535
00:39:49,279 --> 00:39:50,760
as per Miss Mindy's agreement.

536
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:53,840
We are in agreement on this?

537
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:55,560
Yes, agreed.

538
00:39:56,840 --> 00:39:57,840
Yes.

539
00:39:58,560 --> 00:40:00,720
Alright, please sign the documents.

540
00:40:12,972 --> 00:40:13,972
Miss Mindy.

541
00:40:19,448 --> 00:40:20,880
And the witness, please sign here.

542
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:28,200
Thank you.

543
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:32,667
Okay, everyone has signed.

544
00:40:32,667 --> 00:40:35,333
Both the originals and the copies
of these documents

545
00:40:35,333 --> 00:40:37,527
will be sent
to both parties within today.

546
00:40:37,527 --> 00:40:41,013
If you have any further questions
you'd like to ask me,

547
00:40:41,013 --> 00:40:43,206
feel free to reach out.
I'm Tanwarin, your lawyer.

548
00:40:43,860 --> 00:40:47,000
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have to attend to another case.

549
00:40:47,727 --> 00:40:48,727
Thank you.

550
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:56,240
Uh...

551
00:40:56,597 --> 00:40:59,880
I need to use the restroom
for a moment.

552
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:21,000
Thank you for coming today, Liu.

553
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:23,760
I wanted things to be clear too.

554
00:41:24,400 --> 00:41:26,520
With a witness and a lawyer.

555
00:41:26,786 --> 00:41:29,320
We both can have peace of mind.

556
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,360
You forgot this when you moved out.

557
00:41:40,366 --> 00:41:41,560
I'm sorry, Liu,

558
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:44,920
for never telling you,

559
00:41:45,891 --> 00:41:48,480
never being direct about anything.

560
00:41:48,920 --> 00:41:52,600
I just felt like
I didn't want you to be worried.

561
00:41:54,564 --> 00:41:58,710
And I've only just realized that
silence doesn't protect anyone.

562
00:41:59,920 --> 00:42:03,400
It only pushed you away from me.

563
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:11,720
Good luck, Liu.

564
00:42:15,575 --> 00:42:17,080
Same to you, Mindy.

565
00:42:40,854 --> 00:42:44,560
Plumbing is fine. No leaks.

566
00:42:46,685 --> 00:42:50,240
All the lights are working.

567
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:52,440
Is there anything you can't fix?

568
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:56,800
I'd never have guessed
you had a Handyman mode in you.

569
00:42:57,640 --> 00:43:01,280
Hey, not only fixing,

570
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:06,020
laying tiles, painting, plumbing
I've done it all.

571
00:43:06,020 --> 00:43:08,080
If it weren't for
my love of drawing,

572
00:43:08,820 --> 00:43:10,480
I'd be a contractor by now.

573
00:43:10,977 --> 00:43:12,784
If you did,
I wouldn't stop you at all.

574
00:43:12,784 --> 00:43:15,520
Maybe you should stop me a little?

575
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:19,520
The Duckman project is waiting.

576
00:43:19,880 --> 00:43:21,840
Understood, Mr. Artist.

577
00:43:23,548 --> 00:43:25,581
Alright, everything's sorted.
I'll head out now.

578
00:43:25,581 --> 00:43:26,837
I have an appointment.

579
00:43:26,837 --> 00:43:28,963
- Thanks a lot.
- Sure thing.

580
00:43:33,704 --> 00:43:35,598
- Wait.
- What is it?

581
00:43:39,396 --> 00:43:42,646
Watch out for the house spirits.

582
00:43:42,646 --> 00:43:44,593
Ohn!

583
00:43:44,593 --> 00:43:45,752
- Go away!
- I'm off.

584
00:43:48,591 --> 00:43:49,591
Ugh.

585
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:59,520
There's no such thing.
The spirits here are kind.

586
00:44:06,121 --> 00:44:07,868
- Please, come in.
- Thank you.

587
00:44:07,868 --> 00:44:10,214
- Good day, Doctor.
- Hello.

588
00:44:15,485 --> 00:44:16,485
Thank you.

589
00:44:18,760 --> 00:44:20,400
Your blood test results look good.

590
00:44:21,160 --> 00:44:23,360
Your glucose and
HbA1c levels are fine.

591
00:44:23,843 --> 00:44:26,120
All your lipid profiles
are within the normal range.

592
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:28,303
That's great news.

593
00:44:28,760 --> 00:44:32,160
Adjusting my diet and
exercising really does help.

594
00:44:32,723 --> 00:44:33,730
Excellent.

595
00:44:33,730 --> 00:44:36,462
If you keep this up consistently,
it will be even better.

596
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:39,360
I have to thank
the person beside me too.

597
00:44:39,360 --> 00:44:41,400
He drags me out
for a walk every morning.

598
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:43,000
I wouldn't have made it otherwise.

599
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:45,613
Keep taking care of
each other like this is great.

600
00:44:46,163 --> 00:44:47,360
Yes, sir.

601
00:44:52,228 --> 00:44:55,299
I have to nail it this time.

602
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:58,440
It's got to be in one take.

603
00:45:18,339 --> 00:45:20,266
- Ouch!
- Hey!

604
00:45:20,266 --> 00:45:21,617
- Ohn.
- Ouch.

605
00:45:22,101 --> 00:45:24,408
Ohn, are you okay?

606
00:45:24,408 --> 00:45:26,336
Easy, easy. Are you hurt?

607
00:45:26,361 --> 00:45:28,728
I think I danced a bit too hard.

608
00:45:28,728 --> 00:45:33,308
You just saw the doctor.
Do we need to go back?

609
00:45:33,308 --> 00:45:37,428
No, some muscle rub should do.

610
00:45:37,428 --> 00:45:38,928
We'll see how it is tomorrow.

611
00:45:38,928 --> 00:45:40,375
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

612
00:45:40,375 --> 00:45:42,481
- You're okay?
- Yeah, no more doctor.

613
00:45:42,481 --> 00:45:44,480
Go sit over there first.
Get up slowly. You okay?

614
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:45,775
I've got it.

615
00:45:45,775 --> 00:45:47,320
Easy, easy.

616
00:45:47,760 --> 00:45:48,979
Take it slow.

617
00:45:49,003 --> 00:45:52,000
Here, use this, a cold compress.

618
00:45:53,741 --> 00:45:54,840
Here we go.

619
00:45:55,265 --> 00:45:58,687
Cold compress. This side, right?

620
00:45:59,514 --> 00:46:02,101
Let me see, how bad is it?

621
00:46:02,101 --> 00:46:03,800
- Hey, wait!
- Oh, sorry!

622
00:46:03,800 --> 00:46:06,193
Not that high, you crazy!

623
00:46:06,193 --> 00:46:07,284
Kidding.

624
00:46:07,284 --> 00:46:09,584
Just checking where it hurts.
Is it here?

625
00:46:09,584 --> 00:46:11,239
Right here?

626
00:46:11,239 --> 00:46:13,092
Keep this on.

627
00:46:13,092 --> 00:46:14,979
See? You pushed yourself
too hard, didn't you?

628
00:46:14,979 --> 00:46:17,960
Your body is protesting.

629
00:46:17,960 --> 00:46:20,360
So you have to
rest for a while, okay?

630
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:22,140
- Okay. Thanks, Jee.
- Right here.

631
00:46:22,140 --> 00:46:23,720
Mmm...

632
00:46:29,459 --> 00:46:31,352
Hey! The soup!

633
00:46:31,352 --> 00:46:33,049
- Oh no!
- Whoops!

634
00:46:33,049 --> 00:46:34,160
Ouch!

635
00:46:34,160 --> 00:46:36,873
- Look at what you're doing!
- Sorry, sorry!

636
00:46:37,584 --> 00:46:39,800
My soup, my soup!

637
00:46:41,520 --> 00:46:42,640
Are you okay?

638
00:46:43,267 --> 00:46:44,267
Okay.

639
00:46:46,128 --> 00:46:47,320
Is the soup okay?

640
00:46:47,320 --> 00:46:49,200
Completely bland, I guarantee it.

641
00:47:01,692 --> 00:47:02,692
Beat the eggs.

642
00:47:07,304 --> 00:47:08,304
Hey!

643
00:47:09,335 --> 00:47:10,335
Dark soy sauce?

644
00:47:11,242 --> 00:47:12,400
It doesn't matter.

645
00:47:30,080 --> 00:47:34,013
Rahu-style steamed eggs.
Sweet and umami.

646
00:47:39,160 --> 00:47:40,160
Mmm.

647
00:47:42,240 --> 00:47:43,720
Tasted like soy sauce noodles.

648
00:47:55,920 --> 00:47:57,880
What will our future hold?

649
00:47:58,520 --> 00:48:00,320
What do you mean?

650
00:48:00,817 --> 00:48:04,309
Well, life as we get older.

651
00:48:04,481 --> 00:48:05,481
Hmm?

652
00:48:13,799 --> 00:48:18,760
It's not just about
preparing money or health.

653
00:48:19,920 --> 00:48:22,400
But we also have to
prepare ourselves for the fact

654
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:25,040
that it could all
change at any time.

655
00:48:30,988 --> 00:48:33,240
Hmm, well...

656
00:48:34,842 --> 00:48:36,560
I guess no one really knows.

657
00:48:38,966 --> 00:48:40,480
When we're old…

658
00:48:41,542 --> 00:48:42,960
what are we going to face?

659
00:48:45,786 --> 00:48:47,840
- That's true.
- Mmm.

660
00:48:49,880 --> 00:48:51,880
And when we're older...

661
00:48:52,960 --> 00:48:55,280
what kind of house
would you want to live in?

662
00:49:00,560 --> 00:49:02,040
A two-story wooden house.

663
00:49:02,641 --> 00:49:04,600
But I think...

664
00:49:05,720 --> 00:49:07,000
A two-story house...

665
00:49:08,004 --> 00:49:11,360
the stairs will be a struggle
once we're really old.

666
00:49:13,925 --> 00:49:15,000
Then a single story.

667
00:49:15,800 --> 00:49:19,720
But there has to be
a fish pond and trees all around.

668
00:49:21,152 --> 00:49:25,629
A porch on the east side so we can
wake up and walk in the sun.

669
00:49:25,629 --> 00:49:30,880
And, a small kitchen for cooking.

670
00:49:32,200 --> 00:49:35,767
I once talked to
Thai and Chon about this.

671
00:49:35,767 --> 00:49:37,160
- Mmm.
- That...

672
00:49:37,160 --> 00:49:40,047
when we're old
and if we have no one,

673
00:49:40,743 --> 00:49:44,520
we'd rent a house together
and share rooms.

674
00:49:44,840 --> 00:49:47,720
But it must have
a very large central hall.

675
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:53,305
Don't fall asleep yet.

676
00:49:53,305 --> 00:49:54,345
Hmm?

677
00:49:55,769 --> 00:49:58,200
In our house, I want...

678
00:49:59,302 --> 00:50:01,055
one room for dance practice.

679
00:50:01,055 --> 00:50:04,920
So I don't have to dance
next to your fish pond, okay?

680
00:50:07,989 --> 00:50:09,002
Is that okay?

681
00:50:09,451 --> 00:50:12,200
Okay. No problem.

682
00:50:15,840 --> 00:50:17,440
Let's exercise tomorrow.

683
00:50:19,160 --> 00:50:20,880
Okay.

684
00:50:25,238 --> 00:50:28,960
- Sweet dreams.
- Goodnight.

685
00:50:33,256 --> 00:50:34,800
- Night, night.
- Night.

686
00:51:40,440 --> 00:51:41,680
Go to sleep already, Mindy.

687
00:51:42,280 --> 00:51:46,640
This is way better than sleeping in
a sleeping bag under a desk.

688
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:51,160
Today is better.
Tomorrow will be even better.

689
00:51:51,993 --> 00:51:54,640
Sleep, Mindy, sleep.

690
00:52:09,240 --> 00:52:11,880
"I'm still scared."

691
00:52:12,880 --> 00:52:15,720
"Scared of getting old.
Scared of getting sick."

692
00:52:16,868 --> 00:52:18,281
"Scared I won't be able to walk."

693
00:52:19,560 --> 00:52:23,080
"Scared that one day,
I might have to walk alone."

694
00:52:27,880 --> 00:52:31,640
But being scared means
we still want to go on.

695
00:52:33,683 --> 00:52:36,960
In a new phase of life
that might not be fun,

696
00:52:38,160 --> 00:52:39,360
but is still worth exploring.

697
00:52:42,288 --> 00:52:45,880
As for what comes next...

698
00:52:47,880 --> 00:52:48,880
I really don't know.

699
00:52:51,080 --> 00:52:52,280
Just keep walking.

700
00:52:54,440 --> 00:52:55,440
Rest when you're tired.

701
00:52:56,200 --> 00:53:00,500
And if one day I trip,
I hope everything I've prepared

702
00:53:01,369 --> 00:53:06,400
physically, mentally,
our friends, and our relatives

703
00:53:07,320 --> 00:53:09,320
our savings, and social security,

704
00:53:09,320 --> 00:53:12,220
will act as a cushion before...

705
00:53:13,072 --> 00:53:14,800
and during retirement.

706
00:53:19,160 --> 00:53:22,360
If you're scared,
just take a deep breath.

707
00:53:27,200 --> 00:53:28,400
It might not be easy...

708
00:53:30,906 --> 00:53:32,280
but it could still be pleasant.

709
00:53:35,205 --> 00:53:37,800
Let's go to sleep for tonight.

710
00:53:38,920 --> 00:53:40,206
We'll deal with tomorrow later.

711
00:53:42,760 --> 00:53:43,760
"Okay."

712
00:53:53,720 --> 00:53:56,040
What happened last night?
Why were you crying like that?

713
00:53:56,600 --> 00:53:57,600
Can you tell me?

714
00:53:58,030 --> 00:53:59,150
I don't know.

715
00:53:59,150 --> 00:54:01,690
I just felt like a failure
in so many ways.

716
00:54:02,440 --> 00:54:04,920
This resume and artwork...

717
00:54:05,520 --> 00:54:06,800
is it out of date?

718
00:54:07,880 --> 00:54:11,480
Are you crazy? A puppy love?

719
00:54:12,360 --> 00:54:13,360
Jum?

720
00:54:20,563 --> 00:54:22,000
Can you ever forgive me?

721
00:54:24,583 --> 00:54:29,560
♪ Can you feel
that love still remains? ♪

722
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:35,800
♪ Can you feel
the stories we made? ♪

723
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:41,016
♪ No matter what stood in our way ♪

724
00:54:41,016 --> 00:54:44,689
♪ Come rain or shine ♪

725
00:54:44,689 --> 00:54:49,838
♪ Can you feel
the love from the start? ♪

726
00:54:49,838 --> 00:54:56,040
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

727
00:54:56,040 --> 00:55:01,720
♪ Calling out so we never part ♪

728
00:55:01,720 --> 00:55:06,200
♪ Every day together
Forever you and I ♪

729
00:55:06,200 --> 00:55:11,200
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

730
00:55:11,200 --> 00:55:16,167
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

731
00:55:16,167 --> 00:55:18,184
Subtitle by Trirat Trakulphat
